verbose_text: There was no difference between those patients receiving treatment with or without LGS in final mean HbA 1c level (7.7 +/- 0.7% vs. 7.8 +/- 1.5%; P = 0.9) or median SH rate (0.0 [0-0] vs. 0.0 [0-2.0]; P = 0.3), but three patients were transferred onto LGS pumps after having SH on standard CGM and did not have any further episodes.
